msIdentifier.repository: Kislak Center for Special Collections, Rare Books and Manuscripts

msContents.summary: Contains three drafts (two partial) of Coniecturarum et opinionum liber, a commentary on Propertius, Tibullus, and Plautus, later printed as Coniecturarum liber in Paris in 1612, as well as fragments of Lucilius and Naevius with interlinear commentaries.

msItem.title: Joannis Passeratii Coniecturarum et opinionum liber
Veterum poematum qua divulsa ac lacera supersunt tomus alter, f. 118r

support.watermark: Briquet Colonne 4433 (1564), Briquet Chien 3639 (1563), Briquet Lettre. B 8079 (1580).

supportDesc.extent: 182 leaves : 328 x 225 mm. bound to 333 x 235 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, i + 182 + i; modern foliation in pencil, lower right recto. Each work except the second has separate contemporary pagination: work 1, p.1-41 is f.1-21, p.42-74 is f.25-41, p.74-79 is f.41v-44, p.80-118 is f.49-68, p.119-157 is f.71-90; work 3, p.1-20 is f.106-115v; work 4, p.1-130 is f.118-182v.

layoutDesc.layout: Work 2 has 45-65 lines per page, work 3 has 45-55 lines per page, work 4 has 23-27 lines per page, all with bounding lines in lead.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in a semi-Gothic cursive (works 1-3) and humanistic cursive (work 4) script, possibly by Jean Passerat.

decoDesc.decoNote: Engraved print portrait of Jean Passerat, probably dating from 1598, pasted into this codex (f. i verso).
Engraved portrait, Jean Passerat, Flyleaf 2 verso

origin.p: Written in Paris, France between 1572 and 1599 (Zacour-Hirsch).

history.provenance: Possibly sold in the collection of L.-J.-N. Monmerqué by L. Potier (Paris), 12 May 1851, lot 2818 (Schoenberg Database of Manuscripts).
